function [pdf]=gaussmultpdf(z,m,C);% gaussmultpdf              - multivariate Gaussian probability distribution function (Jan 1,2001)%% Compute the value of the multivariate Gaussian probability% distribution function for a vector of values for these% variables. %% SYNTAX :%% [pdf]=gaussmultpdf(z,m,C);%% INPUT :%% z      n by 1   vector of values for the Gaussian distributed variables.% m      n by 1   vector of means for the variables.% C      n by n   symmetric covariance matrix for the variables.%% OUTPUT :%% pdf    scalar   value of the probability distribution function computed%                 for the z vector of values.n=size(z,1);A=((2*pi)^(n/2))*sqrt(det(C));pdf=exp(-0.5*(z-m)'*inv(C)*(z-m))/A;